        <front>
            <div type="abstract">
                <head>Abstract</head>
                <p>A facile and environment-friendly solvothermal method has been developed for the
                    controlled growth of nano- and micro-structured trigonal selenium (t-Se) by
                    using green templates. And, the morphology of trigonal selenium can be tuned by
                    using different kinds of templates. The as-obtained products were characterized
                    by X-ray powder diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscope (SEM).
                    Furthermore, the formation mechanism of trigonal selenium nano- and
                    microcrystals was rationally suggested. This method will open a new avenue to
                    synthesize other functional inorganic nano- and microcrystals.</p>
